	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I don't know what the price will be this time.
<br />
<br />I missed the first run, but I'm definitely getting one this time.  It'll be useful to me for testing/repairing Squeedo carts after they get built, in case a BIOS update ever fails before completing (a reset vector of $FFFF could lead to some BRK-dancing, heheh).
<br />
<br />Most NES mappers have their registers in the program address space, and there aren't many exceptions other than Squeedo and maybe MMC5.  So a RAM cart with a mapper would need a way to know the difference between being re-written and handling mapper register writes.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


