	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">Memblers wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Most NES mappers have their registers in the program address space, and there aren't many exceptions other than Squeedo and maybe MMC5.  So a RAM cart with a mapper would need a way to know the difference between being re-written and handling mapper register writes.</div>
<br />
<br />How does the CopyNES dump the ROMs to begin with?  I thought it needed special mapper-specific code for dumping a game using a specific mapper.  So putting ROM data back onto a cart modified to have RAM in place of the ROM would require mapper-specific code, right?  So reading ROM data is just as hard as writing ROM data?

		

		</td>
	</tr>
